dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Yosu, Korea. In upper left margin: Korea city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic Projection. Relief shown by 20 meter contour intervals and spot elevation. Polyconic projection. Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reishauer system, Japanese form of Korean names (shown in parentheses) transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. Relief shown by contours, spot heights and hachures. Depths shown by soundings. "Contour interval 20 meters." "Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reischauer system, Japanese forms of Korean names (shown in parentheses) transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." "Height in meters, depths in fathoms at nearly lowest low water." "5-45." Three classes of roads or trails, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Some buildings are named. Includes glossary to Korean, Japanese and English terms. Military grid. AMS 1.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
